criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Residents in permanent accommodation in participating nursing homes during the
             inclusion period;

          -  Residents in accommodation in nursing homes with similar catering services and who are
             not supplied with Bleu Blanc Coeur® food or who are supplied with at most 2 BBC
             products per week;

          -  Affiliation to a social security scheme;

          -  Consent signed by the resident or the person in charge of the representative

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  ADL-LFS score on inclusion >19;

          -  Exclusive enteral nutrition;

          -  Protection of effective justice;

          -  Lack of understanding of the French language;

          -  Estimated life expectancy of less than 12 months on inclusion, estimated by the
             attending physician or, if there is one, the nursing home physician.

          -  Only for the ancillary actimetry study: residents under guardianship or unable to
             self-manage.
